---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="About | The Deliberate Man" description="The philosophy behind The Deliberate Man." />
	</head>
	<body class="flex flex-col min-h-screen">
		<Header />
		
		<main class="flex-grow max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 w-full">
			<article class="prose prose-lg prose-neutral max-w-none">
				<header class="mb-12 text-center">
					<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-serif font-bold text-brand-black mb-6 leading-tight">
						About
					</h1>
					<p class="text-brand-darkgray uppercase tracking-widest text-sm font-bold">
						The Deliberate Man
					</p>
				</header>
				
				<div class="divider"></div>

				<div class="text-brand-darkgray font-sans text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-6">
					
					<!-- 
					========================================================
					ABOUT ME
					======================================================== 
					-->
					
					<p>
						I created <strong>The Deliberate Man</strong> for men who know there must be more.
					</p>

					<p>
						For years, I wrestled with many of the same questions that quietly haunt thoughtful men in middle age:
					</p>

					<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 py-4 text-brand-black font-medium">
						<li>What is the point of all this?</li>
						<li>Why does achievement so often fail to satisfy?</li>
						<li>Why do so many men become comfortable, distracted, and spiritually asleep?</li>
						<li>How do we build a life that actually feels meaningful?</li>
					</ul>

					<p>
						I searched widely—through philosophy, psychology, self-development, discipline, and lived experience. What I discovered was simple:
					</p>

					<p class="text-xl font-serif text-brand-black border-l-4 border-brand-black pl-4 py-2 my-8">
						Most of what men are chasing externally already exists within them.
					</p>

					<p>
						Purpose is not something handed to you.<br />
						Meaning is not hidden in money, status, or endless consumption.<br />
						Fulfillment is built through discipline, reflection, courage, useful action, strong relationships, and deliberate living.
					</p>

					<p>
						This platform exists to help men stop drifting through the second half of life.
					</p>

					<p>
						My work blends timeless philosophy, practical discipline, secular wisdom, and honest reflection for modern men who want more than shallow success. I believe a good man should strive to become disciplined, wise, useful, courageous, curious, and morally grounded.
					</p>

					<p class="font-bold text-brand-black">
						You do not need to become someone else.
					</p>

					<p>
						You need to wake up to what is already within you—and build a life you respect.
					</p>

					<p>
						If you feel restless, unsatisfied, or aware that life is passing too quickly, that feeling may not be failure.
					</p>

					<p class="font-bold">
						It may be awakening.
					</p>

					<p>
						Welcome to <strong>The Deliberate Man</strong>.
					</p>

					<p class="text-center font-bold tracking-widest uppercase mt-12 text-brand-black">
						Live deliberately. Choose meaning. Remain curious.
					</p>
					
					<!-- 
					========================================================
					END OF "ABOUT ME" TEXT
					======================================================== 
					-->

				</div>
			</article>
		</main>
		
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
